AbathurBaseVar3.description: Abathur, the Evolution Master of Kerrigan's Swarm, works ceaselessly to improve the zerg from the genetic level up. His hate for chaos and imperfection almost rivals his hatred of pronouns.

AbathurMecha.description: Humanity had never considered that sentient machines could exist in the darkness beyond the earth. From distant stars, Abathur's Xenotech invaders came to plunder the earth's resources and further their evolution.

AlarakBaseVar1.name: Crimson Alarak
AlarakBaseVar1.description: Not all heroes are born of altruism... some, like Alarak, simply desire vengeance. As the new Highlord of the Tal'darim, Alarak leads his people to a destiny free of the corrupt influence of the fallen xel'naga, Amon.

AlarakDark18.description: In the forgotten darkness beyond reality, a new avatar of primordial power has been forged. This dark mirror of Alarak's malice and sadism seethes with contempt toward all of existence... including its own.

AlarakHunter.searchText: Herald of N'zoth Alarak Crossover Black
AlarakHunter.description: The God of the Deep writhes within his prison, thrashing endlessly. Alarak, the Corruptor's Herald, brings word of the Old God's return, preparing all realities for the coming change.

AlarakUltimate.description: The Highlord's armor serves as both ceremonial adornment and as a conduit of raw power. Adorned with blood shards and fueled by terrazine, it channels Alarak's fury directly into his blades.

AlexstraszaBaseVar1.name: Saronite Alexstrasza
AlexstraszaBaseVar1.description: Alexstrasza, the queen of dragons, was empowered by the titans to be the guardian of all life on Azeroth. She has aided mortals time and again, even at great personal cost. Now, she soars across the Nexus, protecting life wherever she finds it.

AlexstraszaDark.description: Sealed away by the Star Princesses millennia ago, the Dark Queen of the Dragons has finally broken free of her imprisonment. At long last, she will have her revenge on the people of Earth.

AmazonBaseVar1.description: After shattering the Worldstone, the young Amazon Cassia had changed. She had seen hatred, terror, and destruction firsthand. If the Askari were to survive the coming darkness, they needed an army. She would begin their training immediately.

AnaArmy18.name: Sidewinder Ana
AnaArmy18.description: As Viper's deadliest sniper, Sidewinder is personally responsible for killing the organization's most prominent enemies. Were it not for her, Viper may never have risen to power... a fact that she uses to her advantage whenever she is contested.

AnaBaseVar1.description: As a founding member of Overwatch and one of the world's best snipers, Ana Amari uses her skills to protect the innocent. Though she went MIA after losing her eye, Ana's sense of duty and responsibility has brought her back to the fight.

AnduinBaseVar1.name: Darkshire Anduin
AnduinBaseVar1.description: As a young man, Anduin sought peace as a priest of the Holy Light and an envoy of the Alliance. After his father, Varian, fell to the Burning Legion, Anduin took up the crown as High King of the Alliance. He soon learned that peace must be fought for, even in the Nexus.

AnduinSciFi19.description: As threats mounted against his nation, Neo-President Wrynn authorized the production of an all new line of mecha. Should evil descend from the stars once more, MechaStorm will have the full strength of Neo-Stormwind behind them.

AnubarakCyberNeonSkin.name: Neon Cyb'arak Anub'arak
AnubarakCyberNeonSkin.description: The defense mecha Cyb'arak, originally designed by Frozen Throne Technologies, was acquired as part of a merger with Jigoku Cybernetics and now patrols the streets, searching for enemies of the corporation.

AnubarakCyberSkin.name: Cyb'arak Anub'arak
AnubarakCyberSkin.description: The Defense mecha Cyb'arak designed by Frozen Throne technologies has proven instrumental in the defense of the African continent against the Kaijo monsters.

AnubarakCyberSkinBlue.name: Cobalt Cyb'arak Anub'arak

AnubarakIce.name: Frozen Anub'arak
AnubarakIce.description: Once a proud nerubian king, Anub'arak dared to stand against the Lich King's invasion, but despite his bravery, he too fell to the unrelenting Scourge. Resurrected into undeath, the Traitor King now serves as a towering weapon of destruction.

AnubarakUltimate.name: Underking Anub'arak
AnubarakUltimate.description: A Spider Lord's carapace has been known to deflect blades, arrows, and even siege weaponry all on its own. When fitted with armor, it is all but unstoppable.

AnubarakZerg.description: Anub'alisk was evolved to safeguard the birthing colony of Cavir from any threats. After the second Overmind's death, the Lurker Lord remained feral until he was recovered by Abathur and Mukav's rogue brood.

ArtanisBaseBlack.description: Despite his relative youth, Artanis was named Hierarch of the Daelaam after the fall of Aiur. Driven by the promise of a brighter future, he hopes to reclaim the protoss' fallen home world and rebuild their once glorious civilization.  Artanis is FREE to purchasers of StarCraft® II: Legacy of the Void™

ArtanisPurifier.description: Shortly after reactivation, Artanis purged Aiur of the protoss in an act of open rebellion. Now the Hierarch of the Purifiers leads his people on a quest to cleanse the sector of all organic life.

ArtanisSkinRonin.description: The Daelaam Shogunate is not blind to its people's suffering. Artanis, the newly appointed Shogun, has sworn to bring the Lenassa to justice before another clan falls to their dark blades.

ArtanisUltimate.name: Hierarch Artanis
ArtanisUltimate.description: As hierarch, Artanis strives for unity among his people. Drawing inspiration from the cultures of both Aiur and Shakuras, his ceremonial armor is a symbol of their combined strength.

ArtanisZeraBlade.name: Daelaam Artanis
ArtanisZeraBlade.description: The Khala is lost, and the war against Amon rages across the Koprulu Sector. Aboard the Spear of Adun, Artanis and his forces are the last hope against annihilation.

ArthasBlue.name: Saronite Arthas
ArthasBlue.description: Once the crown prince of Lordaeron, and protégé of Uther the Lightbringer, Arthas was corrupted by the cursed blade Frostmourne in a bid to save his people. Now he rules over the damned as the Lich King and all shall know his wrath.

ArthasCrimsonCount.name: Crimson Count Arthas
ArthasCrimsonCount.searchText: Crimson Count Arthas Raven Court Hallow's End Black Red
ArthasCrimsonCount.description: Few of Sarah von Kerrigan’s suitors are as bold or brash as Marquis Arthas du Menethíl. The Crimson Count hopes their unholy union will spell doom for Raven Court’s Vampire Slayers.

ArthasFrostWyrm.searchText: Frost Wyrm Arthas Altered Fate Blue
ArthasFrostWyrm.description: After the death of the Ashen Verdict's champions, none could halt the Lich King's advance. As a reminder of his victory, he grafted the bones of his fallen servants onto his armor.

ArthasGuanYu.searchText: Mystic Kingdoms Arthas Guan Yu Green Gold
ArthasGuanYu.description: Revered for his bravery and martial skill, General Arthas has led his king’s armies to countless victories. His loyalty knows no bounds, and nothing can make him break his oath of service.

ArthasUltimate.description: As Frostmourne devoured more and more souls, the Lich King's dominion over the damned grew ever stronger. It wasn't long before his armor began to manifest changes.

AurielBaseVar1.name: Dusk Auriel
AurielBaseVar1.description: It is through the archangel Auriel that the power of hope flows into the fabric of creation. Her eternal light illuminates even the darkest souls. Seeking harmony in all things, she is a mediator, a counselor, and when the need arises, a fearless warrior.

AurielDemonic.description: An angel can never truly become a demon. But once the Lord of Hatred corrupted Auriel's spirit and bound it within a mistress of the Burning Hells, most mortals would struggle to tell the difference.

AurielHanamura.description: For centuries, viewing cherry blossoms at the start of spring has been a time-honored tradition. Auriel was the first omnic to join in the festivities, and has done so every year since she started.

AurielWCAV.description: Spirit Healers are impartial arbiters of life and death and it takes a considerable injustice for one to choose a side and go to war. Auriel's presence has granted a new hope to the Alliance.

AzmodanAzguldan.description: Gul'dan could feel the demon's blood coursing through his veins... Mannoroth's gift once set the orcs on their path, now Azmodan's gift would make them unstoppable.

AzmodanBaseVar3.description: The Lord of Sin rules over a densely populated land of Hell where both the greatest joys and despair, and the deepest depravities can be experienced. But it is never enough for Azmodan, who has set his eyes on the realm of Sanctuary.

AzmodanMadAxe18.description: For years, Dominus Vile has served the mad warlord Garrosh as the general of his warband. His mutants scour the wastes, raiding outposts and bringing their master whatever their simple minds can conceive of having value.

BarbarianBaseVar3.name: Angelic Sonya
BarbarianBaseVar3.description: From the frozen Dreadlands of the north come the mighty Barbarian warriors. After surviving the destruction of her home and death of her tribe, Sonya wanders Sanctuary in search of battle and a better life for her people.

BarbarianBaseVar4.name: Nephalem Sonya
BarbarianBaseVar4.description: With the Worldstone's destruction, a new generation of Nephalem arose. They were descended from both angels and demons, yet stronger than both. It was not long before the Nephalem's glory was fully realized.

BarbarianBlue.name: Dreadlands Sonya
BarbarianBlue.description: From the frozen Dreadlands of the north come the mighty Barbarian warriors. After surviving the destruction of her home and death of her tribe, Sonya wanders Sanctuary in search of battle and a better life for her people.

BarbarianDeathKnightFemale.name: Death Knight Sonya
BarbarianDeathKnightFemale.description: Sonya wandered the outskirts of the Nexus, desperately seeking a way to avenge her fallen people. The power Kel'Thuzad offered was worth any price, even binding her soul to the Scourge for eternity.

BarbarianSummer18.description: After losing the heavyweight belt last year, La Pantera has come back to Nexomania seeking revenge. Now only the undefeated La Parca stands in her way. Will she return to glory? Or does her rise end here?

BrightwingMonarch.description: Just like the flawless butterfly from which she takes her name, Monarch Brightwing has many ways to sting. Kneel peasant! For you face the Monarch! And her wrath is cruel...

BrightwingUltimate.name: Fey Dragon Brightwing
BrightwingUltimate.description: The fey magic from which Brightwing draws her power is wild and chaotic. Her very form reflects its unstable nature, ever shifting, like an image from a dream.

ButcherBaseVar3.description: An unrelenting hacking echoed off the walls of the Cathedral and as Prince Aidan made his way through its depths, the sound only grew louder. There were no screams; just that dreadful sound... over and over.

ButcherButcherlisk.searchText: Butcherlisk Butcher Machines of War Crossover Purple
ButcherButcherlisk.description: Abathur's newest creation was inspired by the tenacity of the hellish abominations he encountered in the Nexus. Its instructions were simple: Acquire fresh essence. Evolve.

ChenGreen.description: To be a brewmaster is to be an explorer, a lover of nature, and when the need arises; a powerful fighter. For years Chen Stormstout has wandered the world of Azeroth in search of rare ingredients, stirring stories, and of course, good brew.

ChenHat.name: Brewmaster Chen
ChenHat.description: Why do we fight? To protect home, and family. To preserve balance, and bring harmony. For Chen, the true question is: What is worth fighting for?

ChoBaseVar1.description: Cho’gall is one of the most powerful, intelligent, and insane ogre-magi to have ever lived. As the leader of the Twilight's Hammer the two brothers seek to bring about an age of destruction... whenever they aren’t bickering that is.

CrusaderBaseVar3.description: There have been many women who have borne the name Johanna in service of the crusade, and each has given her life to purify her faith. Johanna carries on their legacy as she searches the kingdom of Khanduras for the fallen star.

CrusaderBaseVar6.description: With the Worldstone's destruction, a new generation of Nephalem arose. They were descended from both angels and demons, yet stronger than both. It was not long before the Nephalem's glory was fully realized.

CrusaderCenturion.name: Centurion Johanna
CrusaderCenturion.description: At Emperor Severus's command, an entire legion marched against the portal of the gods. All but one returned home, a single centurion taken as punishment for man's hubris.

CrusaderEnforcer.description: To join the Specialized Tactical Operations and Rescue Missions (STORM) Unit, agents must meet drill sergeant Johanna's daunting requirements. Her family's long legacy as STORM officers makes it hard to impress her.

DeckardArmy19.name: Deckard Pain
DeckardArmy19.description: As the United States signed the Malta accords, their sovereignty ended, and Viper's began. Yet, in secret, Maj. Pain had been given leadership over a team with a very particular set of skills and one final mission: resistance.

GuldanBaseVar1.name: Legion Gul'dan
GuldanBaseVar1.description: Abandoning the ways of shamanism, Gul'dan entered a pact with the demon lord Kil'jaeden and betrayed his people in exchange for limitless power. With the orcish Horde under his master's thrall, both Draenor and Azeroth nearly fell into his grasp.

GuldanDark18.description: The avatars of the Dark Nexus are twisted reflections of heroes and villains. While they may wear familiar guises, they are, in truth, chaos and hatred incarnate... an ancient evil that can only be bargained with: never controlled.

GuldanSpider.description: The Balespider's Burning Vestments were woven from the cinderwebs of the Red Widow, Beth'tilac. Only by enduring the flames of the Firelands can a Warlock know its searing embrace.

GuldanUltimate.description: With his deception complete, Gul’dan need no longer hide his face beneath a cowl. He is Darkness Incarnate, and all of the Nexus shall behold his true power in the war between shadow and light.

HanzoArmy19.description: Cpt. Shimada had his mission: to eliminate the Viper leader known as Deathfang, his brother. The government expected him to fail, but they made a mistake... they didn't realize they were dealing with Hanzo.

HanzoBaseVar1.description: Once heir to the Shimada clan's criminal empire, Hanzo abandoned his birthright after he almost killed his younger brother. He now strives to perfect his skills as a warrior, and sees the Nexus and its endless conflict as the ideal training ground.

IllidanBaseVar3.description: Illidan Stormrage, the first demon hunter, betrayed his people and created a new Well of Eternity after the demonic invasion of Azeroth. Now Illidan lords over Outland slaying unsuitably prepared Heroes who venture into his domain.

IllidanLunar.searchText: Lunar Illidan Lunar New Year Red Lunar Festival
IllidanLunar.description: For most of the year, Illidan loathes druidic customs. But during the Lunar Festival, even he sets aside old grudges and joins his brother in honoring the departed elders of the Stormrage family.

IllidanShando.description: Stormrage was born with amber eyes; a sign of great destiny... But as he learned from Cenarius, his brother grew distant. Still, none expected Malfurion's betrayal.

IllidanUltimate.description: The Blades of Azzinoth had served Illidan as dutiful companions while he tracked his prey across the Nexus... perhaps these Man'ari warplates would as well, in time.

IllidanWar3.description: Free after ten thousand years, Illidan would sacrifice everything in order to defeat the Burning Legion, prove himself superior to Malfurion, and redeem himself in the eyes of Tyrande.

ImperiusDemonic19.name: Demonic Imperius
ImperiusDemonic19.description: The Lord of Wrath is said to be the greatest warrior in the Burning Hells. His limitless anger is nearly uncontainable: an unholy inferno that would see all life consumed by its profane flame.

ImperiusVar1.description: Leader of the Angiris Council and Aspect of Valor, Imperius has valiantly led the armies of the High Heavens to innumerous victories over the demons of the Burning Hells. While his methods are exact and severe, there is no greater defender of righteousness in the entirety of creation.

JainaBaseVar3.description: Once the apprentice of the Archmage Antonidas, Jaina Proudmoore led the survivors of Lordaeron to Kalimdor and founded the city of Theramore. Now, she serves the Alliance as a powerful voice fighting for reason and diplomacy.

JunkratBaseVar1.searchText: Orange Black White Stripe Jail Prison
JunkratBaseVar1.description: The destruction of the Australian omnium left the area an irradiated waste and survivors like Jamison Fawkes were greatly affected by radiation. Now as the explosive-obsessed criminal Junkrat, he is renowned for leaving havoc and bedlam in his wake.

JunkratFallen.description: The junkrats are the most scarcely seen of the fallen family of demons. Capricious and suspicious to a fault, they prefer to live amongst the ruined war-machines that litter Pandemonium where they scrounge for resources.

LeoricJanitor18.description: Once Raven Crest's star alumnus, the Skeleton King's baseball career was cut short when he dramatically shattered his shin trying to steal home in the '96 Nexus Multi-World Series. Now, he cleans up after your lousy kids.

LeoricKingVrykul.name: God-King Leoric
LeoricKingVrykul.description: King Leoric used his legendary might to strike down every jarl who challenged his ascent to the throne. But not even uncontested rule is enough to slake his thirst for power.

LeoricRed.description: Madness. Betrayal. Death. These are the legacy of the Black King Leoric's reign. Driven to madness by the spirit of Diablo, Leoric brought untold suffering on his kingdom. Even after his death there was no release for the Skeleton King.

LeoricSpace.name: Space Lord Leoric
LeoricSpace.searchText: Space Lord Leoric Super Black Red
LeoricSpace.description: The Space Lord has brought countless worlds to heel in the name of the Eternal Empire. Soon, even the Earth's troublesome Star Princesses will fall to the power of the darkness.

LiLiExplorer.description: The Explorer's League is known for their progressive stance on accepting members of all races into their ranks. If you've got a heart that longs for adventure and discovery, you're in!

LiLiLunarBlack.name: Eclipse Lunar Li Li
LiLiLunarBlack.description: Each new year brings with it untold promise. It is a joyous time when we honor those who came before us, while celebrating the endless possibilities ahead of us.

LucioUltimate.description: Vishkar's sonic technology was a good starting point, but the pursuit of perfection in sound quality demands keeping up to date with the latest in audio equipment.

LunarJaina.searchText: Lunar Jaina Lunar New Year Red Lunar Festival
LunarJaina.description: In recent years, all of Azeroth has celebrated the yearly Lunar Festival in honor of their elders. Jaina is no exception. In times when the future is uncertain, it's important to honor the past.

MaievBaseVar1.name: Ivory Maiev
MaievBaseVar1.description: Maiev Shadowsong stood watch over the imprisoned Betrayer for ten thousand years, and hunted him relentlessly after he was released. Some say she's determined; others say she's obsessed. Either way, she will stop at nothing to ensure the security of her world.

MaievHellWarden.description: Demonic "justice" is cruel and sadistic. The Hellwardens who serve Andariel understand that inflicting physical pain upon their prisoners is not enough. True anguish comes from torturing the mind and soul.

MaievSpooky18.searchText: Red Gold Purple Witch Hallow's End
MaievSpooky18.description: Deep in the underbelly of the Raven Tower lies a prison filled with traitors and miscreants brought to justice by the Spider Warden. Now, at the Raven Lord's behest, she hunts down the Heroes summoned to protect King's Crest.

MalfurionBasePurple.name: Raven Malfurion
MalfurionBasePurple.description: Malfurion Stormrage is the greatest druid on Azeroth, and a student of the demi-god Cenarius. Communing with nature and Cenarius through the Emerald dream, Malfurion protects the wilds from demonic influences.

MalfurionBetrayer.searchText: Betrayer Malfurion Altered Fate Black Blue
MalfurionBetrayer.description: Sargeras's whispers of power were impossible for the broken Malfurion to resist. She had called him "Betrayer"... Soon, they would all call him Master.

MalfurionFlame.description: Majordomo Stormrage felt the change instantly. Though only a small spark, it was enough to signify his incantations had finally broken through. When the Firelord arrived, the Nexus would burn.

MalfurionPurpleStormrage.description: Although Broll Bearmantle had saved the Archdruid's life, it had cost him his own. Even now, Malfurion wears his armor to remind himself of the sacrifices that saved Hyjal.

MalfurionWinter.description: With little else to do once the creatures of the wild begin their long hibernation, Malfurion has taken to celebrating the Feast of Winter Veil as the jolliest shan'do of all.

MalGanisBaseVar1.name: Undercity Mal'Ganis
MalGanisBaseVar1.description: Cunning and intelligent, Mal'Ganis was chosen to bring Arthas Menethil into the Lich King’s service. After manipulating the prince into purging Stratholme of life, he finally fell to Frostmourne as Arthas's first act as the Lich King's champion... yet a demon does not die so easily.

MalGanisPilotHawk.description: The Dreadmachine armor provides industrialist Malcom Ganis with incredible strength and a staggering ordinance. Sure, it may draw power from an alien's heart, but only minor hallucinations have occurred... so far.

MalthaelBaseVar1.description: Once the Aspect of Wisdom, Malthael abandoned heaven after the Worldstone's destruction. In secret, he had resolved to end the Eternal Conflict by becoming a Reaper of Souls and eliminating everything affected by demonic corruption, including humanity.

MalthaelMecha19.description: With Mecha Tyrael destroyed, Neo-President Anduin Wrynn knew the return of the Xenotech was inevitable and had prepared accordingly. But could two untested mecha pilots possibly defeat the enemy known as the “Reaper of Worlds”?

MalthaelWinter17.description: Also known as the Ghost of Winter Veil Yet-to-Come, Malthael offers those he visits in the cold dark night a glimpse of their future. Unsurprisingly, their "future" is always death.

MarshallRaynor.description: Once the Confederacy mined Mar Sara dry of resources, the colonists became desperate. Marshal James E. Raynor found himself alone, trying to keep the peace on a world in chaos.

MasterNazeebo.name: Hellflame Nazeebo
MasterNazeebo.description: The Hellflame Mask was created in honor of Nazeebo's victory over the Prime Evil. Trusting no one else to guard the black soulstone, he kept it close... Perhaps, too close.

MedicApothRed.description: The Royal Apothecary Society's experiments have resulted in many alchemical discoveries, which Apothecary Morales administers to soldiers in the field. Some side effects may occur.

MedicBaseVar3.description: To good marines, the only thing more important than the rifle in their hand is the medic at their back. As one of the first officers deployed during the United Earth Directorate's invasion, Lt. Rosa Morales is the best of the best.

MedicEnforcer.description: Officer Morales, STORM Unit's newest recruit, is wholly committed to supporting the city's civilian populace as well as her fellow agents. Thanks to her medical training, she is perfect for the unit's emergency response team.

MephistoStarWraith.description: The Eternal Empire is built upon conquest and servitude, but not all planets submit easily. Upon the Star Lord's command, the legion of Star Wraiths descend upon rebellious worlds leaving only scarred husks in their wake.

MephistoVar1.name: Hollow Mephisto
MephistoVar1.description: Dul’Mephistos, the Lord of Hatred, is said to be the most cunning among his brethren. Even while imprisoned in a soulstone, his vile influence corrupted the Zakarum and manipulated them into breaking the seal, giving him free reign to reunite the Prime Evils and enslave humanity.

MonkBaseVar3.name: Northern Kharazim
MonkBaseVar3.description: To the monks of Ivgorod, the gods are in all things, and their divine will is proclaimed by the Patriarchs. With unshakable faith, Kharazim carries forth the decrees of the thousand and one gods to the ends of Sanctuary and the realms beyond.

MonkBaseVar4.name: Nephalem Kharazim
MonkBaseVar4.description: With the Worldstone's destruction, a new generation of Nephalem arose. They were descended from both angels and demons, yet stronger than both. It was not long before the Nephalem's glory was fully realized.

MonkClaws.name: Berserker Kharazim
MonkClaws.description: Though his memories elude him, Kharazim knows that his past is marked by his feral rage. Thankfully, the Hellfire Cabal provides the perfect target for his aggression.

MonkJade.description: Wielding Shi'ron's Sacred Flames is an honor given only to the Grandmaster of the Jade Dragon order. In martial combat, Kharazim has no equal in all of the Onyx Empire.

MuradinKandyKing.description: Everyone wants to be King of Kandy Mountain... but once a Gummy Dragon shows up, they flee to Sugar Plum Valley like the rest. Heavy is the head that wears the cupcake crown.

NecromancerBaseVar1.description: From the recesses of the eastern jungles comes a man cloaked in mystery. As a member of the secretive Priests of Rathma, or the Necromancers, Xul wields powerful death magic and fights to preserve the delicate balance between order and chaos.

NovaGreen.description: November "Nova" Terra is a ghost of the Terran Dominion and one of the most powerful psionic soldiers ever known. Nova is highly focused, determined, and extremely deadly. Even Jim Raynor wouldn't want to be caught in her crosshairs.

OrpheaBaseVar1.name: Regal Orphea
OrpheaBaseVar1.description: Rejecting the dark power her father had begun to consort with, Orphea tried to run away from the Raven Lord's influence. But after witnessing King's Crest fall to his machinations, she was convinced she needed to stand and fight. She now vows to protect the innocent--as a Hero of the Nexus.

RagnarosBaseVar1.name: Scorching Ragnaros
RagnarosBaseVar1.description: As the lord of Azeroth’s fire elementals, Ragnaros desires nothing more than to burn the world to ash. Banished to the Firelands eons ago, the Firelord now turns his rage toward the Nexus, intent on incinerating everything and everyone within it.

RagnarosLil.description: YOU FOOL! WHAT DID I SAY ABOUT SUMMONING ME TOO SOON? I DESPISE BEING ADORABLE!

RehgarBaseVar3.description: Rehgar Earthfury has seen his share of combat, both as a gladiator, and a master of his own team. Now, having put that life aside, he serves as a simple shaman of the Earthen Ring, earning his redemption by healing the lands of Azeroth.

RehgarGFWinter.description: Some people believe that Great-father Winter is just a symbol of commercialization created by Smokeywood Pastures. Those people get coal shoved up their stockings.

RehgarUltimate.description: Long ago the spirit of Lo'gosh revealed itself to the orc clans of Draenor. To this day his ferocity and feral instincts still serve as a guide to the shaman of the Earthen Ring.

RexxarBaseBrown.description: It was a strange twist of fate that led the wandering half-ogre Rexxar to the fledgling city of Orgrimmar. With his aid, Thrall and the Horde were able to secure their homeland and defend it from the invading forces of Lord Admiral Daelin Proudmoore.

RexxarMarine.description: The terrans are descended from Earth's exiled prisoners, mutants, and degenerates. Some, like the military ursine-handler Cpl. Rex Arkk, are more genetically aberrant than others.

TassadarArgent.description: An Executor without equal, Tassadar has fought tirelessly to purify the Koprulu sector of zerg infestation. Only now, after learning to wield the power of the void, is Tassadar finally ready to face the Overmind and its all-consuming Swarm.

TassadarMecha.description: The Kaijo Diablo could not be contained; cities worldwide had been reduced to cinders. Now humanity's survival hangs upon the untested mecha, Tassadar.

TassadarUltimate.description: Executors rarely command from the field of battle, but their Regalia is fitted with meticulously crafted khaydarin crystals to amplify their psionic powers should the need arise.

ThrallEarthbreaker.name: Earthbreaker Thrall
ThrallEarthbreaker.description: The weight of the world hangs upon the Aspect of Earth, a burden no mortal can bear. As Thrall embraced its power, he was consumed by living rock and forever changed.

ThrallHellhammer.name: Hellhammer Thrall
ThrallHellhammer.description: Go'el, the new Warlord of the Ashwolf clan, lifted the shattered Doomhammer from the Blackrock chieftain's corpse. Of his father's betrayers, only Gul'dan remained.

ThrallHellhammerGreen.name: Felhammer Thrall
ThrallHellhammerGreen.description: Go'el, the new Warlord of the Ashwolf clan, lifted the shattered Doomhammer from the Blackrock chieftain's corpse. Of his father's betrayers, only Gul'dan remained.

ThrallRed.name: Mag'har Thrall
ThrallRed.description: As a child, Thrall served the cruel Aedelas Blackmoore as a slave. After gaining his freedom, he guided the liberated orcs to a land of their own and worked to recover their ancient traditions. Now and forever he is the Warchief of the Horde.

ThrallSilver.name: Silver Thrall
ThrallSilver.description: As a child, Thrall served the cruel Aedelas Blackmoore as a slave. After gaining his freedom, he guided the liberated orcs to a land of their own and worked to recover their ancient traditions. Now and forever he is the Warchief of the Horde.

ThrallUltimate.description: The vestments of a shaman should be as simple as the elements themselves. Although, there's no rule about what you wear beneath them.

TinkerAzure.name: Sewage Gazlowe
TinkerAzure.description: Few would consider Gazlowe a fighter, but what he lacks in height, he makes up in mechanical know-how. Besides, you don't get to be boss of a "boom"-town like Ratchet with just a charming personality, if you know what I mean.

TracerGhost.description: Most who undergo training at the Ghost Academy come out of it with a grim outlook on life. The fact that Tracer didn’t is a testament to her mental and emotional fortitude.

With the ability to alter her own time at will, she fights the good fight wherever she goes--even the Nexus. Don't worry, loves. The cavalry's finally here.  Tracer is FREE to purchasers of Overwatch™: Origins Edition

TyraelBlue.name: Platinum Tyrael
TyraelBlue.description: Among the angels it is the Archangel of Justice Tyrael who is humanity's greatest defender. Wielding his sword El'druin against the Burning Hells, the Prime Evils would have enslaved humanity long ago if Tyrael had not intervened.

TyraelDemonic.name: Demonic Tyrael
TyraelDemonic.description: Of all the Aspects of Sin, Tyrael, the Lord of Pride, is the most ruthless. His every action and every thought serves only to fulfill the desires of his true master: himself.

TyrandeBlack.description: Tyrande Whisperwind strikes fear into all who wish ill of the Kaldorei. As the highest ranking Sentinel and High Priestess of Elune, she is not only the night elves' most deadly warrior, but also their most cunning leader.

TyrandeBloodElfBase.searchText: Blood Elf Tyrande Altered Fate Red
TyrandeBloodElfBase.description: Named for her ancestor, the first Sun Queen, Tyrande Windrunner serves the blood elves as their Ranger General, preparing them for their pilgrimage into Outland.

TyrandeSuper.description: When the Eternal Empire destroyed her home planet, Tyrande Solarwind swore to avenge her fallen people. Now, her quest to eliminate her mortal enemy has led her to the city of New York.

TyrandeUltimate.description: The vestments of the Sentinel General were blessed by Elune herself. Like the night elves before the World Tree's fall, they do not age and remain as pristine as when they were blessed.

TyrandeWarden.name: Warden Tyrande
TyrandeWarden.description: Ever since they were children, Tyrande had known her fate was bound to that of Malfurion's. Now, she would serve as his warden, and for his betrayal the sentence would be eternal.

TyrandeWardenBloodElf.name: Sun Warden Tyrande

UltimateCrusader.name: Sacred Oath Johanna
UltimateCrusader.description: The crusader's armor is an emblem of their identity. Over the centuries it is constantly molded and reshaped to fit the needs and personality of its current master.

UtherAzureJudgement.name: Blessed Judgment Uther
UtherAzureJudgement.description: Despite surviving Arthas's brutal assault, Uther was unable to prevent Lordaeron's fall. Now under Varian's banner he leads the Silver Hand into Northrend to mete out justice.

UtherBlackHand.name: Black Hand Uther
UtherBlackHand.description: The first paladin and founder of the Order of the Silver Hand, Uther the Lightbringer is a faithful servant of the Light. Dispensing justice with the swing of his hammer, Uther is a bastion of truth and an unflinching symbol of the Alliance.

UtherJudgement.name: Judgment Uther

UtherJudgement.description: Despite surviving Arthas's brutal assault, Uther was unable to prevent Lordaeron's fall. Now under Varian's banner he leads the Silver Hand into Northrend to mete out justice.

UtherLumberjack.name: Lumberjack Uther
UtherLumberjack.description: Arthur Light of British Columbia had barely sipped his coffee when he was dragged into a Nexus portal. Now, he fights alongside the greatest of heroes, hoping to find a way home.

UtherSulfuron.description: With the Firelord extinguished, the mighty Sulfuras has found a new champion to wield its molten power. When the new Firelord arises, Uther intends to smite it with its own hammer.

ValeeraBaseVar1.name: Wraith Valeera
ValeeraBaseVar1.description: For a time, the gladiator Valeera Sanguinar served dutifully as one of Varian Wrynn's personal bodyguards. Now, her shadowy skills find her a natural fit within the secretive rogue order, the Uncrowned, in their fight against the Legion.

ValeeraVampire.description: Not all of Raven Court's vampires swear fealty to the Raven Lord. The one known only as "V" has launched a solitary crusade against her own kind, making her an unlikely ally of the Vampire Slayers.

ValeeraWCAV.description: While Valeera's allegiances may be her own, her friendship with Varian meant she couldn't allow him to go to war alone. If he was going to fight the Horde, she would be his blade in the dark.

VallaUltimate.description: Demon hunters share few traditions as each walks their own unique path... but a master passing on their armor is an honor few refuse. Valla would wear Josen's mantle with pride.

VarianBaseVar1.name: Iron Varian
VarianBaseVar1.description: Few would have expected that the gladiator known only as Lo'Gosh was in truth the missing ruler of Stormwind, Varian Wrynn. Now the High King of the Alliance, his every action shapes the destiny of Azeroth itself.

VarianCommandant.description: As chief security officer for Volskaya's Nexus operations, Varian Volkov is no stranger to harsh winters and cold steel. Rather than pilot a Svyatogor mech, he prefers to meet his foes face-to-face.

VarianLogosh.description: After awakening on the shores of Durotar, the gladiator known as Lo'Gosh became a star of the Crimson Ring Arena.  Rumor has it that he fights with the fury of the Ghost Wolf himself.

VarianUltimate.searchText: Master Varian Blue Gold Grey Gray
VarianUltimate.description: The Lion has long been associated with the nation of Stormwind and the House of Wrynn. It is a symbol of courage, dignity and ferocity; truly befitting for the High King.

VarianWCAVFoot.description: Sergeants browbeat unruly recruits with tales of a footman named Varian who refused promotion again and again, despite slaying hundreds of foes, because he preferred to remain on the front lines.

VarianWCAVGrand.description: Rallied by the Lady of Thorns' call, Grand Marshal Varian Wrynn left Stormwind with both his father's blessings and army in tow. The Alliance would not let Alterac fall to the Raven Lord's machinations.

WhitemaneBaseVar1.name: Vengeful Whitemane
WhitemaneBaseVar1.description: As the High Inquisitor of the Scarlet Crusade, Sally Whitemane zealously leads her champions in a neverending war against the undead. Under her guiding Light, all who have been touched by the plague of death will be purged by her cleansing flame... no matter how much they protest.

WitchDoctorBlood.name: Crimson Nazeebo
WitchDoctorBlood.description: With cabalistic incantations and vestments of feather and bone, the witch doctor Nazeebo calls upon spirits from the Unformed Land to aid him. Few outlanders encounter a witch doctor in the flesh, without losing their own.

WitchDoctorGrimskull.name: Grimskull Nazeebo
WitchDoctorGrimskull.description: The Teganze jungles hold many legendary weapons wielded by both man and demon alike. The Grimskull Visage itself has passed from one Witch Doctor to the next since the Sin War.

WitchDoctorGrimskullBlueskull.name: Azure Grimskull Nazeebo

WitchDoctorGrimskullVar4.description: With the Worldstone's destruction, a new generation of Nephalem arose. They were descended from both angels and demons, yet stronger than both. It was not long before the Nephalem's glory was fully realized.

WitchDoctorHarlequin.name: Harlequin Nazeebo
WitchDoctorHarlequin.description: The Countess Kerrigan's demands for entertainment mirror the darkness within her. Her harlequins are masters at manipulating life and death, solely for her amusement.

WitchDoctorMadAxe18.description: In the Warchrome Wastes only Nazeebo's diesel priests can access the secrets held within the high-octane. With a mighty roar, they funnel its fury and combustion into the material world.

WizardLunarVar1.description: To Li-Ming, the Lunar Festival of the Nexus was not so dissimilar from those of her homeland, Xiansai. Donning her favored finery, she joined in celebration with a nostalgic joy.

WizardMaskVar1.description: Few sorcerers are as famed as Tal Rasha, who sacrificed himself to imprison Baal during the Sin War. Those wizards who don his armor do so with the intent to live up to his legend.

WizardSkinStarPrincess.searchText: Star Princess Li-Ming Super Red Blue
WizardSkinStarPrincess.description: For eons, Earth has been protected by the magical Star Princesses. Together, they stand against the evil Eternal Empire and its Space Lords in the name of love and friendship.

WizardSkinStarQueen.name: Star Queen Li-Ming
WizardSkinStarQueen.description: All seemed lost as the star princesses fell one after another. But Li-Ming’s refusal to give up hope awakened a new power inside her, transforming her into the legendary Star Queen.

WizardSkinTemplar.name: Templar Li-Ming
WizardSkinTemplar.description: Li-Ming may be strong-willed, but the will of Templar Li-Ming is stronger.

WizardSkinUltimate.name: Archon Li-Ming
WizardSkinUltimate.description: Once, only wizards who had spent countless hours braving the inferno were able to attain the fabled archon armor. Those who adorned it were both respected and feared. Then came transmog...

WizardSkinVolley.name: Striker Li-Ming
WizardSkinVolley.description: Li-Ming is an avid student of magic, but it was her skills on the court that scored her a scholarship at the Yshari Sanctum. As team captain, she intends to lead the Vizjerei Fireflies to victory.

WizardStarPrincessVar3.description: For eons, Earth has been protected by the magical Star Princesses. Together, they stand against the evil Eternal Empire and its Space Lords in the name of love and friendship.

WizardStarQueenVar1.name: Neo Star Queen Li-Ming
WizardStarQueenVar1.description: All seemed lost as the star princesses fell one after another. But Li-Ming’s refusal to give up hope awakened a new power inside her, transforming her into the legendary Star Queen.

WizardTemplarVar1.name: First Ascendant Li-Ming
WizardTemplarVar1.description: Li-Ming may be strong-willed, but the will of Templar Li-Ming is stronger.

WizardTemplarVar2.name: Dark Templar Li-Ming
WizardTemplarVar2.description: Li-Ming may be strong-willed, but the will of Templar Li-Ming is stronger.

WizardUltimateVar1.name: Lovely Archon Li-Ming
WizardUltimateVar1.description: Once, only wizards who had spent countless hours braving the inferno were able to attain the fabled archon armor. Those who adorned it were both respected and feared. Then came transmog...

WizardUltimateVar2.name: Shadow Archon Li-Ming
WizardUltimateVar2.description: Once, only wizards who had spent countless hours braving the inferno were able to attain the fabled archon armor. Those who adorned it were both respected and feared. Then came transmog...

WizardVar1.name: Crimson Li-Ming
WizardVar1.description: The derogatory moniker "wizard" is often given to mages with rebellious attitudes or an obsession with power. Li-Ming displays a little of both and she's hardly ashamed of it. After all, who are they to judge a wielder of limitless arcane magic?

WizardVolleyVar1.name: Scarlet Striker Li-Ming
WizardVolleyVar1.description: Li-Ming is an avid student of magic, but it was her skills on the court that scored her a scholarship at the Yshari Sanctum. As team captain, she intends to lead the Vizjerei Fireflies to victory.

WizardVolleyVar2.name: Canary Striker Li-Ming
WizardVolleyVar2.description: Li-Ming is an avid student of magic, but it was her skills on the court that scored her a scholarship at the Yshari Sanctum. As team captain, she intends to lead the Vizjerei Fireflies to victory.

WizardVolleyVar5.name: RCHS Striker Li-Ming
WizardVolleyVar5.searchText: Orange Teal Raven Court High School
WizardVolleyVar5.description: Li-Ming wasn't always the super-star of the Fireflies. Until her varsity year, she was seen as the troublemaker of the RCHS volleyball team. It was only with the help of some new friends that she changed her rebellious ways.

YrelBaseVar1.name: Crystalforged Yrel
YrelBaseVar1.description: After traveling to an Alternate Draenor, the forces of Azeroth saved the acolyte Yrel from the Iron Horde. With their aid, she rose to the rank of Exarch and fought back the demonic invasion of her world. Now, she finds herself where time, space, and dimensions converge: the Nexus.

YrelJester.description: Not all villains have super powers. Some, like the Jester gang, spread chaos and mayhem using whatever weaponry they can steal. While you don't have to be mad to join their ranks, if you do... you probably are.

ZagaraBaseVar3.description: If Kerrigan is the Queen of the Zerg, then Zagara is the mother of the brood. Cunning and tenacious, she commands her minions on the field of battle. Encounter her brood and beware: Mess with her children, and you answer to mama.

ZagaraCryptQueen.description: Within the Nexus are an infinite number of universes and an infinite number of undead to recruit into the Lich Lord's army. Crypt Queen Zagara now serves as the ultimate living siege weapon of the Scourge.

ZaryaBaseVar1.description: Aleksandra Zaryanova is one of the world's strongest women and was a promising athlete, but all that changed when the Siberian omnium reawakened. As a soldier in the Russian Defense Force, she now proudly uses her strength to protect the ones she loves.

ZaryaSpooky18.description: The Black Knights have served as the mercenary protectors of Raven Court since age immemorial. It is only natural that their commander, Zarya, the Phantom Knight, serves as one of the four generals of the Raven Lord's army.

ZaryaUltimate.description: The Tobelstein Reactor is an emergent technology, and its full potential has yet to be tapped. Rumor has it that the Gravitic Harness is the next great advancement in energy projection.

ZeratulArgent.name: Crimson Zeratul
ZeratulArgent.description: The enigmatic dark templar Zeratul serves the xel'naga. While he expertly wields the power of the Void, it is his wisdom that earns him the respect of the Koprulu sector's leaders - despite his penchant for dramatic entrances.

ZeratulGem.name: Executor Zeratul
ZeratulGem.description: In his final moments, Zeratul made the ultimate sacrifice to defeat the Overmind and secure victory over the zerg. Inspired by his example, the Templar and Dark Templar are united once more.

ZeratulHighTemplar.name: High Templar Zeratul
ZeratulHighTemplar.description: Despite Judicator Raszagal's warning that only heresy comes from contact with the Dark Ones, Praetor Zeratul believes that this "Tassadar" may be the key to Aiur's salvation.

ZeratulMummy.description: The deserts of Aranoch are inhospitable in the best of times. After Mephisto bound a demonic spirit to the corpse of the Assassin-Prince Zeratul things have grown considerably worse.

ZeratulRonin.description: After failing to protect his lord from the Lenassa clan, Zeratul severed his nerve cords and his connection to his home. Now he wanders, searching for a way to atone for his sins.

ZeratulUltimate.description: Upon selection, each Dark Prelate is presented with a unique armor reflecting their beliefs and personality. Zeratul rarely dons the Shadow's Embrace, as he prefers less formal attire.

ZeratulZergHunter.name: Zerg Hunter Zeratul
ZeratulZergHunter.description: The Zer'atai clan of Dark Templar are renowned hunters. For nearly a millennium, they have wandered across Shakuras, fashioning intricate armors from the bones of their prey.

ZuljinBaseVar1.name: Classic Zul'jin
ZuljinBaseVar1.description: Before the elves and their Alliance, the forests of Lordaeron belonged to the trolls of the Amani empire. As their warlord, Zul'jin has united the tribes into an army that stands ready to take back what is theirs and to slay the elves who stole it from them.

ZuljinLunarVar4.description: For Azeroth's trolls, the loa are a central part of the Lunar Festival. Shadow hunters celebrate the powerful spirits by crafting elaborate masks in their likenesses.

ZuljinUltimate.name: Warbringer Zul'jin
ZuljinUltimate.description: Prior to the Troll Wars, the Amani Empire was a great and powerful civilization. Zul'jin has rekindled the flames of its former warlords, and has donned their ceremonial battle armor as a sign of respect.
